column2: Algal bloom.  Basin virtually devoid of aquatic vegetation.
Migrated from EPA STORET Legacy Database- originally reported by Wisconsin DNR
Windy conditions at time of the reading.
algae bloom well under way- water temp. 76 degrees- no wake ban has been lifted
south west winds 78 degree water temp.
light west winds 81 degree water temp.
calm- cloudy- warm and humid 82 degree water temp.
sunny hot and humid- light west winds- 82 degree water temp- 7 inches of rain - less algae
sunny beautiful- light west winds-82 degree water temp. water clarity better
sunny warm 80 light winds-62 degree water temp- we have had a couple of frosty mornings- I am guessing lake turned over
sunny light winds after 3 days of record winds- 54 degree water temp.
46 degree water temp 50 degree air- west winds- cloudy- ice completely off lake
sw winds heavy chop 51 degree water temp
cool east winds drizzle 45 degree air 51 degree water
gone for the last 2 weeks- came back to hot and muggy 90 degree air 75 degree water- algae bloom going on- water temp up water clarity down with hot weather
severe weather afternoon- tornado in eagle- 86 degree air 78 degree water
light west winds 84 degree air 82 degree water- milfoil treated
sunny 85 degree air 84 degree water- 2 weeks of hot and humid weather- milfoil down- improved water clarity
sunny 80 degree air 81 degree water- milfoil down native weeds making a comeback
sunny- light winds- 78 degree air and water
sunny 25mph NE winds- cold front- 60 degree air 70 degree water
cloudy east winds- light rain 61 degree air- 64 degree water
sunny- light winds- light frost last night- 70 degree air 64 degree water
sunny 70 air-48 water- sw winds- ice off 3-7- record warmth for march- pier in today normally ice on lakes yet- gin clear water hit bottom at 22'
easter sunday-64 air-56 water-north west winds gin clear water
cloudy cool east winds 58 air 53 water- temps back to normal last couple of weeks- lake flies are hatching
south east winds- 80 air 70 water- bluegills spawned males on nest- beautiful day and water
sunny 90 air- 72 water- lake sprayed for milfoil yesterday- second batch of bluegills spawning.     milfoil is by far primary weed in lake is kililng it taking away cover for smaller fish
fathers day- southwest winds- temp. 90 air-79 water- water clarity good- dry no rain conditions continue- male gills still on beds.
85 air- 82 water- finally cooler temp- north east winds have put end to a week of record heat and humidity 100 plus temps. water is still in good shape no blue green algae yet.
property owners meeting today- 90-s air- 84 water temp. hot weather continues

temp 84 water- upper 90-s air- hot and humid- hot muggy conditions continue- southeast winds- water still looks good with slight algae bloom occuring. water level dropping with hot dry weather. warmest year on record through july.
light north winds- temp 81 water 82 air- water in great shape- see a litlle algae floating around- god to see native weeds- water level down about 30" from previous highs with hot dry summer.
temp 71 water mid 80-s air- south winds- another warm day- record warmth all summer- water clarity out standing
sunny- southwest winds- temp 70 air- 62 water- a couple of frosty mornings- water still outstanding.
breezy- temp 65 air- 56 water- lake has turned over- clarity down a bit with turnover.
southwest winds- cloudy- temp 70 air 51 water- rain and cold front tonight- water clarity great after turnover.
pier in today- last reading for the year- light winds- temp air 55- water 40- gin clear water.
south winds- 65 air temp. ice out april 7- alot of rain and cool temp this month
NW winds- 80 air temp. clear water- bass moving in to shallow warmer water
SE winds- 77 air temp. bluegills on beds spawning- weeds up
SE winds- 85 air temp- tested for phosphorus and chlorophyll- lake treated for milfoil
phos. and chlor. test taken.  NE winds 75 air temp beautiful day.  algae bloom still going on.
phos. and chlor. test today.  sunny hot and humid 95 air temp. SW winds. phos. and chlor. test today.  sunny hot and humid 95 air temp. SW winds. native weeds looking good
rain last few days- bluegills starting beds-s.e. winds 80- chlorophyll and phosphorus test done
gills spawning- algae bloom- bluegill kill-cool nights with fish on beds- water temp. drop
phosphorus chlorophyll test- milfoil spot treated- fish survey performed
cool summer continues- n.w. winds 80 sunny- water still under 80
phosphorus chlorophyll test- hot and humid mid 80
cloudy- light north winds- water clearing- fewer native weeds showing up
8 inches of rain first milfoil treatment has been applied
no wake rule on lake due to heavy rain
no wake still in effect milfoil is down water is not clearing up as usual possibly due to lack of weeds
milfoil gone very few weeds hoping for the best that lack of weeds will not hurt fish and that no milfoil will give native weeds a chance to germinate
cloudy rain 52 air temp- no wake in effect-lake level high no milfoil
sunny hot and humid 95 air temp-no wake- lake level high-no milfoil- phosphorus chlorophyll test
sunny humid 83 air temp-no wake. no milfoil-algae in water
sunny humid 84 air temp-no milfoil- no wake- phosphorus chlorophyll test
60-s NEwinds-heat and humidity gone-100 northerns planted today
ice out yesterday- pier in today
cloudy 40 degrees 52 degrees water temp-crystal clear water- lake level high
cloudy 60 degrees water 67 degrees-cool rainy spring- no wake- water level high- townline flooded
water test- sunny 70 degrees- no wake- bluegill spawning
water test- cloudy humid 82 degrees- lake level down a bit- more algae than usual- no weeds
sunny 80 degrees- lake has algae more than usual- no milfoil no native weeds
water test- cloudy 75 degrees- algae later than usual- lack of weeds?? 100 northerns planted
cloudy- more rain- humid 75 degrees- lake level high
